Installing
==========
If you have the big archive you just have to unpack is where you want it.
If you have the updatepackage you need the orginal mesa archive and then
you will nead lha in your path and run the installer script in /amiga 
(or just unpack AMesa.lha yourself)


Compiling
=========
For compiling with gcc you have to enter the command "make aros". Via the 
environment variable LOCALFLAGS you can specify additional optimizations.

ADISP_CYBERGFX is defined in include/gl/amigamesa.h since aros has native
support for CyberGfx.  If u wish to use the normal Amiga Gfx Functions
just remove the define.

